<BaseLayout title="About | Daft-a-Peth" description="The story behind Daft-a-Peth: football, betting, golf, food, Yorkshire-ness and other nonsense.">
  <header class="about-hero"><div class="wrap about-grid"><div><p class="kicker">The story so far</p><h1>Still daft.<br /><em>Just older.</em></h1></div><div class="about-logo"><img src="/logo-daft-a-peth.png" alt="Daft-a-Peth graffiti logo" /></div></div></header>
  <article class="about-body wrap-narrow">
    <p class="big-copy">Daft-a-Peth is what my Gran used to call me as a toddler.</p>
    <p>I was always messing about, always finding something to grab my attention and make her laugh. Not much has changed—my wife now calls me a functional adult toddler, so I’m still Daft-a-Peth.</p>
    <p>Since then I’ve been diagnosed with SMA Type 3, a degenerative muscle condition. I’ve been lucky: a small percentage of people respond well to a trial medication, and for me it has helped stop the deterioration.</p>
    <aside>“Getting back to golf is something I don’t take for granted.”</aside>
    <p>In recent years I’ve managed to get back playing golf. I also had a bit of a mad mid-life career change, going from engineering into the betting industry. I now work for an American-based independent odds compiler and trading house.</p>
    <p>Most of what I do is heavily protected by NDAs, but I’ve written betting pieces under pseudonyms. I enjoy it. Often I need to write just to get ideas out of my head.</p>
    <p>This site is where all of that comes together: football, betting, golf, Yorkshire-ness, food and whatever else I’m into at the time.</p>
    <p class="big-copy orange">It’s not a tipping website.</p><p>If that sounds like your thing, you’ll get it.</p><a class="button button-primary" href="/articles/">Get into the articles</a>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
